@csantanapr  Sure, but fiddling with the manifest and having to restart OpenWhisk every time you make a change to the manifest can be a bit of a hurdle.

Is there anything problematic regarding production deployments that you see with this change, which was mainly intended for development purposes?

As I can see, this fix might also help in case of temporary network errors or docker registry hiccups that would make docker pull fail, but would not make invocations fail unnecessarily as the image would be locally available.

@rabbah @markusthoemmes 
can you help with above. your help and time is greatly appreciated.
Regards
